{title: You Don't Need to Move a Mountain}
{artist: Jeanne Pruett}
{composer: Written by Waylon Holyfield and Jim Rushing}

[C]You would bring me [F]silver and [C]gold
Lay the [G7]world down at my [C]feet
You would weave me a [F]royal [C]robe
You would [G7]bleed and die for [C]me

But you don't need (you don't need) to [F]move a [C]mountain
Tame a raging river or [G7]make your body bleed
You don't [C]need (you don't need) to [F]swim an [C]ocean
Lay your head on my breast and [G7]rest a while with [C]me

You would build me a [F]palace of [C]gold
Catch a [G7]star for my [C]hair
You would tame an [F]angry [C]sea
Just to [G7]prove how much you [C]care

But you don't need (you don't need) to [F]move a [C]mountain
Tame a raging river or [G7]make your body bleed
You don't [C]need (you don't need) to [F]swim an [C]ocean
Lay your head on my breast and [G7]rest a while with [C]me